frameDefinitions: Lexical units in this frame refer to Electricity, in particular as a form of energy harnessed for particular uses (such as powering machines).
An Agent causes Air to move in a direction, usually specifying either in or out of the body.
A Person has a particular mental state and the ability to engage in an activity with enthusiasm, energy, and positivity.
This frame concerns internally undifferentiated Substances.
A Rider is being transported in a Vehicle, or is moving on foot.
A Fire burns Fuel, resulting in damage and possibly complete destruction of the Fuel.
frameExamples: A compound to generate wind <t>electricity</t> was built on the other side of those mountains.
As their gut bacteria ferment cellulose , they generate methane <t>gas</t> , which escapes from the rear ends of the insects.
<t>Mounted</t> police officers are a common sight in this village.
A fire that started on Saturday afternoon, the High Glade Fire - located on the Mendocino National Forest's Upper Lake Ranger District - continued to <t>burn</t> actively on Sunday.
listRoleDefinitions: <fen>Electricity</fen> is the physical force that is used as power.
The <fen>Agent</fen>'s breathing causes the motion of the <fen>Air</fen>.  <fen>Agent</fen> is generally the External Argument.
<fen>Air</fen> is the substance that the <fen>Agent</fen> causes to move.
The time at which breathing occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the breathing occurs.
The person who is evaluated for a level of enthusiasm.
The undifferentiated entity which is presented as having a permanent existence.
The <fen>Rider</fen> is being transported by a <fen>Vehicle</fen>.

The total material currently involved in combustion, including both the parts of the <fen>Fuel</fen> currently undergoing chemical alteration and the partially ionized gas that results from this process.
The entity that is undergoing rapid chemical alteration leading to damage or destruction.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Fire</fen> is burning.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Fire</fen> is burning.
